.TH "SVGTextContentElement.getSubStringLength" "JS" "February 2, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SVGTextContentElement.getSubStringLength \- SVGTextContentElement:
getSubStringLength() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]getSubStringLength()\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]SVGTextContentElement\f[R] interface represents the computed
length of the formatted text advance distance for a substring of text
within the element.
.PP
Note that this method only accounts for the widths of the glyphs in the
substring and any extra spacing inserted by the CSS
\f[CR]letter\-spacing\f[R] and \f[CR]word\-spacing\f[R] properties.
Visual spacing adjustments made by the \f[CR]x\f[R] attribute are
ignored.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getSubStringLength(index, length)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]index\f[R]
An \f[CR]integer\f[R]; the start index of the substring.
.TP
\f[B]length\f[R]
An \f[CR]integer\f[R]; the number of characters to include in the
substring.
.SS Return value
A float.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]IndexSizeError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the \f[CR]index\f[R] is greater than the highest index or
\f[CR]length\f[R] is negative.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Getting the Length of a Substring
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]svg\f[R] width=\[dq]300\[dq] height=\[dq]100\[dq]>
  <\f[B]text\f[R] id=\[dq]exampleText\[dq] x=\[dq]10\[dq] y=\[dq]50\[dq] font\-size=\[dq]16\[dq]>Hello, SVG World!</\f[B]text\f[R]>
</\f[B]svg\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] textElement = document.getElementById(\[dq]exampleText\[dq]);

\f[I]// Get the length of a substring starting at character 0 with 5 characters\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] substringLength = textElement.getSubStringLength(0, 5);

console.log(substringLength); \f[I]// Output: 35.55\f[R]
.EE
